Reasoning: The paper discusses the design of value propositions for co-creation in a complex system of direct and indirect goods service, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and computational complexity (cs.CC) in terms of designing and managing the system. The paper also touches upon customer experience (cs.CE) and social impact (cs.SI) in terms of co-creating value with the customer. Finally, the paper discusses the need for a holistic approach to designing value propositions, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
